    <note type="biography">
        <p>Geologist, publicist, and constitutional lawyer. Lived in the United States, 1837–42; lectured in Boston on phrenology and philosophy. Returned to England and was called to the bar, 1849. Studied geology in his spare time. First president of the Geologists’ Association, 1859. Studied the fossils of the Chalk.</p></note>
